message: Enable source artifact generation in all builds on guava, and use that plus other resources to build the Guava-gwt artifact. Then enable the gwt artifact in the aggregate build.
Add a bootstrap JVM class replacement that overcomes an incompatibility between JDK5/6.  This allows us to compile in such a way that our concurrency code works in J2SE 5 and 6.

message: delete IDEA files, and update .gitignore accordingly
manual sync
- cleanup formatting, and add missing dependencies - use animal-sniffer-maven-plugin to verify 1.5 compatibility
make more tests pass
make all tests pass
specify plugin versions
update artifact names
add javadoc generation
copyright and warning cleanup
add support for jdiff generation
use 'latest' for non-release version
remove unused xerces jar
test updates
- add cache cleanup - scrub @since tags
split configuration out of execution so it will apply to other executions
update scm urls
remove build.xml, and unneeded libs
deprecate throwCause
javadoc cleanup
doc cleanup
use new sonatype parent
Fully qualify @links so that they actually work.
Expose StandardXXX constructors, fixing external issue 701.
Visibility changes.
Add putUninterruptibly and takeUninterruptibly, and use them in the implementation of chain().
Improve @throws InterruptedException documentation for get().
Further Javadoc changes.
Better SerializableTester Javadoc.	Strip reference to internal SerializationChecker from Guava.
Merging BlockingQueues into Queues
Improve Javadoc of ArrayTable methods cellSet() and values()

Inline BaseHolder interface into Holder and Optional. It was causing issues to	Scala users and didn't really serve any purpose anyway. This also makes it	easier to start selectively eliminating some of the methods from Holder if we	want to do that.
Eliminate GWT serialization warnings for HashBasedTable/TreeBasedTable and TreeMultiset.	As of <http://gwt-code-reviews.appspot.com/1544803>, GWT recognizes any annotation named @GwtTransient.
@since tags
Handling paths of the form x/../../b (bug 705)
Implement Range.isContiguousWith(Range), which defines the conditions under which two ranges will be coalesced in RangeSet.
Migrate SortedMaps.transform{Values,Entries} to Maps
Reorganize methods between UnsignedLongs and UnsignedLong.	Make clear in the Javadoc the reasons to use each.
add ForwardingCache
Provide serialization for UnsignedLong
update since to 10
Begin adding "most common element" operations to Multisets.
Add UnsignedInts to primitives.
Move SortedMaps.difference to Maps
Allow nulls in GeneralRange.
implement basic serializability for ComputingCache
make tests of unreleased classes GoogleInternal
Update testers to recognize that null may be a restricted element
Make Bst framework null-compatible when the comparator is
Update primitives package-info
Drop in SortedTreeMultiset in place of TreeMultiset.
allow all write operations on asMap view
Fix ImmutableMultiset 1.6.0u24 compilation error.

Link {Iterables,Collections2,Lists}.transform.	Refer to ForkJoinTask.join from Futures.getUnchecked Javadoc.	Remove an unnecessary cast.	Also, fix a typo in the InterruptedRuntimeException deprecation instructions.
Fix compile problems with Guava.
Eliminate most uses of non-Unicode whitespace in com.google.common tests.

Roll back CL 23327883's very broken FeatureSpecificTestSuiteBuilder optimization. (We don't clone the tests, so we run all methods against the same target class (the last to be initialized).) Fix up newly failing tests (except for CompactIntegerListTest, for which I've filed a bug). Most are problems with the tests themselves: - Test suppressions weren't being carried over to tests of the reserialized collections. - Map values() collections were universally assumed to permit null queries. - EnumSet was asserted to fail fast on concurrent modification. - Many ConcurrentModificationException tests advanced the iterator past the end of size-zero or size-one collections. - It's not possible to create an empty collection that contains null. Empty collections don't contain anything :) - (Bi)MapGenerator.create is passed an Object[] containing Entry objects, not an Entry[]. - (Bi)MapGenerator.create is passed an Object[] containing Entry objects, not an Entry[]. - StandardImplForwardingNavigableMap.keySet() returned a SortedSet instead of a NavigableSet. - StandardImplForwardingNavigableMap implemented lastEntry and descendingSet in terms of one another (using the standard* methods). - Tests of null SortedMultiset values fail when run against a nullsFirst() comparator because the nulls are outside the submultiset ranges tested. - NavigableSets.synchronizedNavigableSet(SafeTreeSet) does not allow null queries. - Tables.transformValues().cellSet() permits remove operations. - collect/testing SmallTests needed their timeout increased. - CompactIntegerListTest didn't specify all the mutation operations it supports. A few are fixed by improvements to production code that arguably aren't strictly "bug fixes": - ConcurrentHashMultiset.removeAll(collectionContainingNull) threw NPE. - Maps.unmodifiableNavigableMap().subSet/headSet/tailSet returned a SortedSet instead of a NavigableSet. - NavigableMaps.unmodifiableNavigableMap().keySet() returned a SortedSet instead of a NavigableSet. - RegularContiguousSet.contains/containsAll threw NPE (which the EmptyContiguousSet equivalents did not). - WellBehavedMap.entrySet().remove(null) threw NPE instead of returning false. (The fix removes the need for Sets.transform.) A few more are real bugs: - TreeMultiset.add(null) succeeded even for comparators that do not permit null. - TreeMultiset.remove(null) failed even for comparators that permit null. - TreeMultiset iterators couldn't remove null elements. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=28001960

Fix GWT behavior of "opportunistic" ImmutableList subclasses. The "standard" ImmutableLists were fine, but Lists.charactersOf() and TransformedImmutableList were broken. Under Java, they inherited working implementations of their methods; under GWT, they inherited versions that forwarded to an empty "delegate" collection. I've overridden all forwarding methods in the GWT emulation in order to avoid this. I've also added tests for charactersOf(), which reveal that GWT String/StringBuilder doesn't perform index checks, so I've added manual checks. TransformedImmutableList could probably stand to have some tests, too, but at least it will be exercised indirectly through the asList() views implemented atop it in Louis's coming CL, which is in fact what revealed these problems. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=28741879

Stop depending on an ImmutableSortedSet quirk in getTypes(): ImmutableSortedSet.copyOf() currently assumes, for a Set input, that there is no need to deduplicate inputs. This is true if the given Comparator if consistent with equals (really, consistent with the original Set's definition of equality). However, if it's not, we can get a set with "duplicates" according to the Comparator. getTypes() depends on this behavior because it sorts by type-hierarchy depth, which is no reason to treat objects as "equal." An upcoming CL will change ImmutableSortedSet.copyOf() to remove this behavior. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=30617067

This CL fixes invalid self-referential collection operations (c.addAll(c), c.removeAll(c), c.retainAll(c), and c.containsAll(c)). Such cases are either no-ops, undefined behavior, or unnecessarily complicated, and often reveal bugs. This an automated fix using error-prone.

Actually fix tearDown handling that was made worse in CL 50062431. - The behavior before that CL was to ignore exceptions thrown by tearDown. - The behavior currently is to exceptions thrown by tearDown unless there was another exception thrown by the test itself, in which case we overwrite the test's exception with the tearDown's exception. - The new behavior is to respect the exception from tearDown unless an exception from the test itself exists to override it. This matches the JUnit behavior. Really.

Remove deprecated, unused, Google-internal Futures.transform overload that accepts a plain Future. The ListenableFuture overloads appear to be serving users well. For those users who are stuck with a plain Future, we still provide Futures.lazyTransform, which has similar but not identical behavior to Futures.transform. Specifically, lazyTransform does not cache the result of the transformation. This could in principle result in Futures whose value changes over time. This, along with the potential costs of repeated function application, is a reason to prefer Futures.transform when possible. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=59754254

When \FFFE, \FFFF, or ASCII control characters are found in the input, replace them with \FFFD. The behavior prior to this CL is to include them in the output (for \FFFE and \FFFF) or to strip them (for ASCII control characters). The characters are not valid in XML: http://www.w3.org/TR/2008/REC-xml-20081126/#charsets ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=65400047

Reimplement legacy RateLimiter as a passthrough to its reimplementation under the new RateLimiter API. I've mostly attempted to leave the behavior untouched, but there are a few changes: - Fixed a bug that would arise with a negative nanoTime() (probably unlikely, but it could happen). - Removed logging. - Stop swallowing interrupts.
Handle overflow and negative timeouts: http://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/issues/detail?id=1622
Change the implementation of Futures.combine to be faster!
Remove the callAllGets 'feature' of CombinedFuture.

Reimplement Throttle as a passthrough to its reimplementation under the new RateLimiter API. I've attempted to leave the behavior untouched (aside from fixing an unsynchronized access to maxTime). ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=65604449

Add AbstractPackageSanityTests.UNDERSCORE_IN_NAME to make it easy to exclude generated classes like AutoValue_Foo from testing. The issue is that these classes typically do not apply @Nullable to the argument of equals(Object), so that they will work when Nullable is not on the classpath. But NullPointerTester requires @Nullable on this argument because otherwise it will fail when equals(null) follows its contract and does not throw an exception. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=73169035

GWT: Better error checking, logging, and documentation. - Error checking: I had been trying to enable compilation with -strict (<https://gist.github.com/Abdennebi/2828230>). However, while the GWT compiler parameter is "-strict" and the Maven system property is "gwt.compiler.strict," the Maven parameter is "failOnError:" <http://mojo.codehaus.org/gwt-maven-plugin/compile-mojo.html#failOnError>. Additionally, while the compilation goal supports failOnError, the test goal does not: <http://mojo.codehaus.org/gwt-maven-plugin/test-mojo.html>. Maven had been ignoring the unrecognized names. - Logging: Turn up the logLevel to make any future problems easier to diagnose. - Documentation: Explain the presence of some scary "Ignored 53 units with compilation errors" warnings. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=74868684

Fix a race: If one input fails at nearly the same time and with the same exception as the *first* failure, we sometimes log the exception, even though it's already propagated into the output. The problem is that the first failure lets subsequent failures proceed before it registers itself in seenExceptions. It does register itself with setException(), but we don't have full atomicity because we have two sources of truth. (This is why we have a problem only when the first failure is involved: Other failures atomically manipulate seenExceptions.) The solution is for whichever caller initializes seenExceptions to propagate it with the value from setException(). This is a little messy but hopefully not too bad. (It comes with a small bonus: It happens to avoid allocating seenExceptions entirely if there is only one failure.) ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=95568611

For public Guava only, rely on the GWT compiler's built-in @GwtIncompatible stripping instead of our custom stripping. The custom stripping dates from the days before GWT 2.6.0 added it to the compiler: http://www.gwtproject.org/release-notes.html#Release_Notes_2_6_0_RC1 This change has been possible for a while, since Guava has required GWT 2.6.1 since Guava 18, but we hadn't had the motivation. Now we do: This lets us avoid checking the stripped sources into Github, which lets us avoid mixing stripped and handwritten sources, which lets us simplify our MOE inverse mappings. Internally, we will continue to rely on the custom stripper for now.

Make a slight tweak to the way we calculate means in StatsAccumulator. We pull out a variable for (value - mean) instead of computing it twice. This also means that we no longer need the old mean to compute the change in sumOfSquaresOfDeltas, we only need the new mean, so we can update mean directly instead of storing nextMean. We end up with the same number of temporary variables and the same calculation but one subtraction fewer and (perhaps more importantly) we do the computations in a more natural order. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=110147656

Remove unnecessary 'unused' variables thanks to an update in the @CheckReturnValue checker. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=113673831

Fix various collections (Sets.union(), Sets.intersection(), Multisets.sum(), etc.) that might overflow when asked for size(). With very large collections, these could potentially return negative (!) results. According to the spec, the result should be Integer.MAX_VALUE:
Graph.java: fix indentation in class-level Javadoc. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=113683678

Add validation that checks that predecessors, successors, in edges, out edges, and all sorts of other relationships are in sync after every test. Add more test coverage for removing edges. This would have caught the breakage in [] ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=113690611
Add @CheckReturnValue to SortedLists. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.

Remove "SetView" from all graph implementations. See [] for why it should be killed with fire. In particular, it made the returned Sets have O(N) (in both time and memory) size() and contains() methods, and in one case, O(N^2) iteration!
Add @CheckReturnValue to the com.google.common.eventbus package. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.
Add @CheckReturnValue to ObjectArrays. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.
Add @CheckReturnValue to MinMaxPriorityQueue. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.

Make Graphs.oppositeNode() slightly more efficient. It performs the same number of equals checks (1 in self-loop case, 2 otherwise) but without the additional call to contains() - while still providing the incidence check.
Reduce memory footprint of mutable graphs by roughly 10%. Considering the increase that [] yielded, getting this back down is definitely good.
Add more consistency checks to AbstractGraphTest. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=113961752
Add @CheckReturnValue to com.google.common.math. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.

Move toString() implementation for graphs to Graphs.java. This is similar to how Graphs.equal() is implemented, and will allow Graph implementations to get toString() for "free". ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=113999189

Replace "DirectedIncidentNodes" and "UndirectedIncidentNodes" with a shared "IncidentNodes" class that implements Set. This avoids the call to .asImmutableSet() that the directed graphs were performing, and also makes it so that we are now very close to having an abstract base graph implementation that will almost entirely replace the 4 current implementations. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=114000977
Some small cleanup to Graphs. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=114030721
Add @CheckReturnValue to DiscreteDomain. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.
Document the requirement that, for directed graphs, incidentNodes iterates as source then target. Move other directed graph specific documentation into DirectedGraph.
Add documentation indicating that the builder mutators returns the same builder object. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=114066331

Add @SafeVarargs to Iterators.forArray (ImmutableList.of() and ImmutableSet.of() are already annotated with this). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=114078599
Use String.isEmpty() in Strings.isNullOrEmpty().
Add @SafeVarargs to Iterators.cycle() (being consistent, since we just added it to forArray()). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=114120886
Release most of UninterruptiblesTest and UninterruptibleFutureTest to Guava. I've excluded the CountDownLatch tests, which are currently intertwined with some other Google-internal tests.
Permit the elapsed time to be slightly shorter than expected. This fixes some flakiness I'm seeing in Guava. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=114130006
Add @CheckReturnValue to collect.Range. This forces the caller of these APIs to "do something" with the result of the call.

message: Let PackageSanityTests run over the entire package (and stop special casing). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=119488117
Followup to "Let PackageSanityTests run over the entire package (and stop special casing)." ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=119501361

Currently, SomeClass<?>.getSubType(SubClass<?, OtherT>) returns SubClass<?, OtherT>. However, if we do NotGeneric.getSubtype(SubClass<OtherT>), we get SubClass as a raw type instead of SubClass<OtherT>.

Add char overload to Joiner.withKeyValueSeparator() to parallel the overload in Splitter.withKeyValueSeparator(). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=119803558

Add @GwtIncompatible. This isn't currently necessary but may be so someday, so I've been trying to establish the practice. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=119881900
Make some of Throwables available under GWT.
Work around Eclipse bug that previously affected GWT and now affects j2objc (with -sourceLevel 8): https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=443596
subType -> "subtype" "superType" -> "supertype"

AbstractServices failure exceptions report what service failed to help with debugging tests with many services. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120232421
Stop using exceptions as flow control in isUriInetAddress().

Reduce the memory usage of Networks by roughly 20%. Delete the IncidentNodes class. Remove (unused) equals/hashcode impl from NodeConnections. Additionally, removeEdge() is now O(1) in all cases (used to be O(D) for networks with parallel edges). edgesConnecting() is now O(1) for networks that dont allow parallel edges (used to be O(D), even though a network without parallel edges cannot return > 1 edge for this method). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120272801
Make mutable directed graphs about 40% smaller. Another nifty benefit: directedGraph.adjacentNodes(node).size() is now O(1). Remove (unused) equals/hashcode impl from NodeAdjacencies.

Update documentation for Interners. Since Java 7, the String.intern() does not allocate the strings in permgen, but instead on the heap (in a table whose bucket size is configurable using XX:StringTableSize).

Add some validation to predecessor/succesor counts. This should also catch the unlikely (impossible?) case where there are more than Integer.MAX_VALUE predecessors or succesors. Alternatively we could change these to longs, but that adds ~8 bytes to every node, and I'm already pretty sure a HashMap cannot hold more than 2^30 entries. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120291028
Support reflection-less atomic updates in AggregateFutureState and InterruptibleTask as in AbstractFuture.

Clean up the impls of edges connecting in the no parallel edges allowed case. Slightly optimize contains() by avoiding constructing an interator. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120347747
Make sure edgesConnecting() is unmodifiable in the parallel edges allowed case. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120348240

Small optimization for node/edge containment. It wouldn't be worth it if nodes()/edges() returned they keysets directly, but wrapping in an unmodifiableset involves an extra object creation and subsequent garbage collection. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120366484
Suppress what will soon be an error-prone compile error internally.

Change name of Animal Sniffer run. The old name includes the version of Java that we're running against. This would otherwise become an unnecessary diff between the Java 8 and Android branches. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120559577

Remove MapMaker.expireAfterWrite(), the expirationQueue, ticker related functionality, and all expirable/evictable related implementation details. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120703596
Delete MapMaker.softValues(). Delete unused NullConcurrentMap and NullComputingConcurrentMap implementations. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120709309

Add spaces to annotations inside comments to prevent them from being interpreted as real code when the file is parsed by tools that behave like the checker framework (see http://types.cs.washington.edu/checker-framework/current/checker-framework-manual.html#annotations-in-comments). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120731063

Delete GenericMapMaker parent class now that generic parameterization is no longer needed (caching APIs are gone). Delete unused NullEntry and AbstractReferenceEntry. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120734317
Add some missing @Beta's for new stuff in 20.0. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120809190
Added NaCL binaries to media type list. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=120819293
Delete warning that TimeLimiter might be changed significantly.
Predicates.subtypeOf, a correctly-named duplicate of Predicates.assignableFrom. Deprecate the latter. Add javadoc.
Fix a minor oversight in using a constant in LongMath for its intended purpose. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121145870
Deprecated Throwables.propagate() ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121375741
Remove @Beta from Throwables.throwIfInstanceOf() and throwIfUnchecked(). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121375812
Adds content security policy (CSP) headers, which are used by older user agents. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121387099

Make the AbstractConfigurable* classes actually abstract. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121411875

Remove emptyIterator() from Guava. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121572091
Expose {Int,Long}Math.isPrime to external users. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=121998832
isPrime: try to improve javadoc ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=122003309
Update public suffix list. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=122019817
Update javadoc of Futures#dereference to point to correct #transformAsync method. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=122184701

Adding WOFF2 media type.

Make iterating through predecessors() and successors() more efficient on directed graphs. Avoids doing a hash lookup for every element in the table. A rough benchmark shows that iteration takes slightly less than half the previous time. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=122853102

Add a fallback in Ordering.leastOf to ensure the worst case of the quickselect component is bounded to O(k log k). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=123038053
Deprecate Ordering.binarySearch. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=123249690
Remove unnecessary string concatenation ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=123253690

message: Bump timeout after recent flaky failure.

Endpoints.java: revert language change in Endpoints.adjacentNode()'s exception message; "does not contain" seems more appropriate even though Endpoints is no longer a Collection.  "is incident to" implies that "Endpoints" is really a misnomer for "Edge", which is sort of OK for Graph but not so much for Network, and "contain" works in both cases.
Rename addEdgeV2() to addEdge().
Use StringBuilder.append(a).append(b) instead of sb.append(a + b) in Iterators.java.
Fix compile-time constant expression overflows

Use BitSet under GWT, as it's now available there. This lets us remove our manual emulation of BinaryTreeTraverser, and it moves us a step closer to allowing precomputed CharMatchers there (if we want to someday, which we might not due to memory concerns).
Update Ordering javadoc to explain the Java 8 situation. Now with branchiness.

Expand test coverage. Make validateGraph() a static method so ValueGraphTest can use it (a MutableValueGraph is a not MutableGraph so it can't extend AbstactGraphTest directly). Move removeEdge_existingEdge() up in the test hierarchy.
Update isCyclic() to work on both directed and undirected graphs. This is part of the effort to move it to Graphs (which I'll do in a followup CL), so we can delete the GraphProperties class!
Add some test coverage.
ValueGraph implementation.

Shift the nodeOrder/edgeOrder methods down in the Graph/Network interfaces. These are definitely "properties" of the graph, and should be under the label as such. Note that the AbstractConfigurable* implementation classes already have the methods in this order.
Delete TestGraphBuilder/TestNetworkBuilder. Remove the testing subpackage from common.graph.
Clean up the javadoc for the mutable graph interfaces.
Fix source links.

Add the methods Graphs.reachableNodes() and Graphs.transitiveClosure(). Three teams have already implemented similar logic! Also, looking through the remaining uses of the legacy Digraph, the only thing preventing many from being converted to common.graph is the lack of transitive closure. So I'd say there's very high demand for this.

Move GraphProperties.isCyclic() to Graphs, delete the GraphProperties class. Rename method to hasCycle(), because isCyclic() implies that it might be O(1). Also to be consistent if we ever add other "has" methods (e.g. hasSelfLoop(), hasTriangleSubgraph(), etc.).

Define equality for Graphs so that a Graph never equals a ValueGraph. This allows ValueGraphs to have the expected behavior when you query valueGraphA.equals(valueGraphB) (i.e. values are taken into account as well).

Delete the unused, @GoogleInternal copy* methods (in particular, copyNodes, copyEdges, and their Predicate-based counterparts). We're missing the ValueGraph version for all of these, and in the copyEdges case, also the Graph version. The Predicate-based methods have the obvious issue that we'd want to release with the Java-8 Predicate, not the Guava Predicate. copyNodes() and copyEdges() have the unfortunate issue of there not being an obvious correct answer for the whether the source or destination should come first in the parameters. And finally, copyEdges() requires us to decide what to do in the event that the destination graph doe not contain the incident nodes (and neither option is particularly intuitive). Overall, we'd rather not have to support these methods at this point.
Add a bit of test coverage for value graphs.

Delete the NodeConnections interface. As an implementation detail we previously took advantage of the shared interface, but that is no longer the case, and such a trivial interface doesn't seem worth keeping around.
Slightly update wording on Graph.equals() javadoc.
Shuffling from internal-only change. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=130430413
Add Hashtable to TestsForMapsInJavaUtil.
Rename "Graph" to "BasicGraph". Flip the inheritance hierarchy. Now, BasicGraph<N> extends ValueGraph<N, Presence>.

message: Make equals/hashcode methods in AbstractGraph/Network final, since changing the behavior of these while still implementing the interface is incorrect.
Update some javadoc. Remove old @SuppressWarnings.
Rename SimpleEdgesConnecting to EdgesConnecting to be consistent with our naming pattern for NetworkConnections (*NetworkConnections and *MultiNetworkConnections).

Change the definition of hashcode for Networks (map of edges to endpoints) to more closely mirror hashcode for Graphs (map of edges to value). Also the map we're basing the hashcode on is now half the size for undirected networks, which is nice (a downside is that isolated nodes don't affect the hashcode, but I'm not too worried about that).
Add more test coverage for Immutable graphs/networks.
Move Network validation into a static method (will be useful for adding Network coverage to MutationTest later).
Remove reference to hypergraphs in test!
Add *degree() methods back to Graph/Network interfaces, with correct formal definition this time (self-loops count twice).

Optimize directed graphs to consume less memory, at the cost of additional code complexity. Some very rough benchmarks also seem to indicate this has slightly faster runtime. I suspect this is due to improved cache performance/locality when using a single Map.
More test coverage for graphs! Test adding and removing nodes/edges repeatedly. Currently only for Graph, will add similar coverage for Network later.
Update some javadoc in the graph builders, add sample code. Run g4 fix on the files.

Completely overhaul top-level javadoc for common.graph interfaces in light of the new interface hierarchy. Spend a lot of time answering what I think will be the #1 question users have: should I use a Graph or a Network? Spend a lot less time defining graph theory terms, that's what wikipedia is for :) plus the method-level javadoc defines terms as necessary. Overall, make it a lot more concise. Javadoc that's too long for anyone to bother reading is just as good as javadoc that doesn't exist!
Update Network.asGraph()'s edge value methods to be consistent with how they're defined in the interfaces. Update tests to fail with the old implementation.
Some more cleanup of javadoc. Add specific language regarding undirected graphs since I feel the behavior there is non-obvious.
Fix compile-time constant expression overflows ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=130697805
Super nit: move allowsParallelEdges() above allowsSelfLoops() in the Network interface (this is the order they're presented in NetworkBuilder, as well as the order in the implementing class).
Fix typo
Expand on "question 3" from the graph/network javadoc, which I felt was a little hard to parse. Also some misc. javadoc cleanup.
Add NetworkMutationTest (parallel to GraphMutationTest).
Change javadoc to refer to Mutable* interfaces. Technically, Graph/Network don't dictate anything when adding edges, because they don't have methods for adding edges.
Slightly update javadoc for inducedSubgraph(). Since edges() has different return type in Graph vs Network, have to use slightly different terminology here.
Fix typo
Fix some stale language in a test.
Make Endpoints implement Iterable.
Delete the unused Graphs.parallelEdges(). Promote Graphs.adjacentEdges (back) to interface method, with a default impl in AbstractNetwork.

message: Change allowsSelfLoops() to default to false for Graph/NetworkBuilder. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=130840045
Fix indentation.

Remove some superfluous checkNotNulls in NetworkConnections. On the nodes/edges, these are internal classes and those parameters have already been checked. On the calls to super.remove*, they've also already been checked.
Minor javadoc tweak.
Add Graphs.transpose() static utility methods for viewing the transpose of a graph. See: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transpose_graph
Return the underlying graph/network for multiple calls to Graphs.transpose()
Prefer hardcoding constant over calculating at runtime.
Add Vector tests to guava-testlib's TestsForListsInJavaUtil
Disabling SelfEquals check for test
Add @Nullable annotations.
NullPointerTester should not require @Nullable on the param of an equals() override
Allow atomic removal of 0 values from AtomicLongMap
Fix bug in Helpers.isEmpty.

Use ArrayDeque and PriorityQueue under GWT (where they're newly available), and provide synchronizedQueue, synchronizedDeque, and MinMaxPriorityQueue there. This also lets us delete our manual implementation of TreeTraverser and avoid LinkedList internally.
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 131198531.
Make nonCancellationPropagating available to GWT.
Add @Beta to new method that hasn't yet been API reviewed.
Make it more difficult to get StackOverflowErrors from hooking chains of futures together with setFuture
Fix typo just because.
Try to explain Sets.newHashSetWithExpectedSize() more accurately and usefully.
Add some javadoc stating that immutable graphs are thread safe.
Fix the serialization of sparse immutable tables.
Changes to common.graph. Sorry for the churn, but after this things should be settled down for a while (and we'll be launching v20 soon!). Changes include:

message: Make the "constructor" methods EndpointPair.ordered()/unordered() public (and make the ones accepting a Graph/Network package-private).

message: Scope an (internal) return type to UnmodifiableIterator.
Add ValueGraph.edgeValues(). Remove ValueGraph.edgeValueOrDefault(node, node).

ValueGraph.java: modify edgeValues() Javadoc to clarify that the behavior of get() if passed an EndpointPair not in the graph is different from the behavior of edgeValue() if passed two nodes not connected in the graph.
Fix Eclipse warning (missing #).
Refactor test utility methods to match graph mutation signatures.
Specify in the javadoc the behavior of Graphs.equivalent() when both parameters are null. Run g4 fix on the file.
Add some missing @Nullable annotations.
guava-testlib: Cover Collections.unmodifiableMap
guava-testlib: Cover checked{,Sorted}{Map,Set}
guava-testlib: Cover Collections.unmodifiableSortedMap()

Eliminate checkNotNulls where they're clearly they're not necessary (i.e. when we dereference the variable on the immediately following line). Also remove the "variableName" message in some of them, particularly when they're internal variables.
Suppress some unused warnings in Eclipse.
Refer to Network references as "network" instead of "graph". Note that we've already started doing this, but (as you can see) are fairly inconsistent with it.
Some minor common.graph tweaks to avoid equals() checks when unnecessary.
Increase test coverage for common.graph. Ensure properties besides just those covered by Graphs.equivalent() are copied over as well.
Rename parameter.

Avoid duplication of code in ImmutableValueGraph. Surprised I didn't realize this sooner :-/ the backing graph is a ValueGraph, so we can just call through. This also let's us do some other nice things:
Move some javadoc out of the graph implementation classes (where we don't really expect people to be poking their noses). Mention briefly in the graph interfaces.
Run g4 fix on all the files in common.graph.
Add a test for passing ListenableFuture<?> instances to whenAllComplete. It doesn't always work as we'd like :(

Swap the nodes of an unordered EndpointPair to prevent callers from relying on the "ordering" of an unordered pair. Remove some superfluous "this." prefixes in ElementOrder (we generally only include "this." when assigning to a member variable).

Clean up some exceptions. In general, the pattern we try to follow is that if the user provides an invalid argument (e.g. a node not in a graph), we throw an IllegalStateException with a detailed error message. If it's an internal method and something is wrong on our end, we throw an IllegalStateException (and don't usually bother with an error message).
Use AssertionError for default case.
Update Public Suffix List. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=132612873
Temporarily allow creation of a CharMatcher from a BitSet for internal purposes. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=132688558
Warn Android users that default Stopwatch behavior may be bad for their health.
Add note about replacements for BYTES constants, isFinite(), and hashCode() methods in Java 8.
Optimize Graphs.transitiveClosure() to avoid copying to a List in the undirected case. Credit to jbduncan for the idea!

Increase test coverage for Networks. Add clarifying statement in javadoc for inEdges() and outEdges(). Modify the sanityCheck method to also check that a set is equals() to its ImmutableSet copy (this will also make sure the set doesn't have duplicate elements).
Add the .vtt type used for HTML5 video subtitles. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=132996392
Add another test for Iterables.removeIf. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=132998224
Fix typo.
Prepare for Java 8.
Add some test coverage for ElementOrder.comparator().
Improve docs on the FluentIterable-Stream connection (part 1).
RegularImmutableSet extends ImmutableSet.Indexed.
Optimization of RegularImmutableMap.
Update an @link in javadoc.
Try to explain the Stream equivalent for filter(Class) a little better. (And stop caring about the paltry benefits of `e -> e instanceof Foo` over `Foo.class::isInstance`.)
Avoid using "i.e." in first sentence of javadoc so the javadoc generator doesn't prematurely cut off the summary.
Delete MapConstraints.constrainedBiMap()

message: Fix imports in all Guava packages.
Fix typo in javadoc.
Fix another typo in javadoc.
Make flaky test less likely to flake. The test currently fails if a thread stalls for more than 50s. I've increased that to 9999ms.
Delete MapConstraints.constrainedMultimap()
breakingChanges: BC[kind=METHOD_REMOVED, impactedSymbol=com.google.common.collect.MapConstraints.constrainedMultimap(com.google.common.collect.Multimap<K,V>,com.google.common.collect.MapConstraint<? super K,? super V>), newSymbol=]

message: Create TreeTraverser.using().
Some additional test coverage for undirected graphs + minor cleanup.
Remove Constraint stuff from package-info.
Delete MapConstraints.notNull()
Some cleanup in EndpointPairIterator.
Small refactor of AbstractGraph.edges() (move to inner class instead of anonymous class).
Increase GWT test timeout. Apparently the GWT Maven plugin considers tests to have succeeded if they time out!
Tell Travis to wait for Maven to finish.

Use ArrayDeque and PriorityQueue under GWT (where they're newly available), and provide synchronizedQueue, synchronizedDeque, and MinMaxPriorityQueue there. This also lets us delete our manual implementation of TreeTraverser and avoid LinkedList internally.
Remove the offset and size fields from RegularImmutableList.
Put scary doc on hashString and less scary doc on hashUnencodedChars.
If File.exists throws an exception when constructing a ClassPath instance, ignore that entry in the classpath rather than propagating the exception.
Bump Travis timeout. It's still too low, e.g.,
Update GWT deps to 2.8.0-rc2.
HostAndPort.java: Deprecate getHostText() in favor of getHost(). ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=133907054
Fix a typo.
Remove a stray 'the'.
Fix comment that had gone out of date.
Increase GWT timeout again.
Increase more timeouts to reduce test flakiness, as in CL 133260276.
Javadoc improvement(?) pass to Function/Functions. To be continued.

Assorted cleanup of cancellation: - Eliminate our overrides of interruptTask() (other than one in a test of interruptTask()). - Make cancel() final under GWT. - Simplify a few tests. - Add or improve boilerplate comments about visibility of fields.
Add edgeValueOrDefault() method to ValueGraph interface, and remove Map-returning edgeValues() for now. This CL effectively rolls back []
Add paragraph to javadoc for Network.edgesConnecting().
Tweak Network.edgesConnecting() javadoc so people don't think it returns a path of edges.
Update Mockito version to 2.1.0-RC.1

Use an anonymous class for AbstractGraph.edges() This was changed recently ([] because of some planned changes we ended up going a different direction with, so now I think it makes more sense inlined.
Change some javadoc to reference node U and V in the context of connectivity (to be consistent with methods on EndpointPair).
Remove redundant String.format call
Apply IntelliJ-suggested language feature migrations.
Replace unnecessary StringBuilder calls with String concat
Remove unused imports
Remove reference to a deprecated method
(partial) Automated g4 rollback of changelist 134687034.
Apply a handful of automated "returns @Nullable" suggestions.
Remove CharacterFilter(BitSet) along with CharMatcher.fromBitSet, which was introduced as a temporary helper for the migration. (partial rollback of CL 132688558, plus some additional changes)
Replace unnecessary StringBuilder calls with String concat
Remove ancient `@Beta` annotations, making these APIs "final". (They can still be removed via 2-year deprecation cycle.) Also touched up a bit of javadoc here and there.
Implement edgeValue() via edgeValueOrDefault() instead of vice versa. For edgeValue() this is the same efficiency, but makes edgeValueOrDefault() perform fewer hash lookups.

Migrate users from HostAndPort.getHostText() to HostAndPort.getHost(). These methods behave identically, but the former name is deprecated. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=134844363
Fix particularly unfortunate typo in ValueGraph javadoc.
Fix typo in ValueGraphBuilder.
Update Mockito version to 2.1.0
Update removal target for APIs that should be removed in 20.0 but which actually won't be.
Remove stale links from 'Learn about Guava'
usage of American English spelling for "license"
No need to disable doclint completely. Disabling high-level HTML issues should be enough
Skip GWT tests on Travis. They're just too slow.
Rewrite MutableClassToInstanceMap to avoid using ConstrainedMap. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=135408484

message: Delete constraints APIs.
Add @since 20.0 to BaseEncoding.canDecode.
Updated Guava README to mention Guava 20.0-rc1.
Shuffling from internal-only change.
Remove Iterator tester infrastructure, which has never had any real tests. (We do perform IteratorTester-based testing through CollectionIteratorTester and ListListIteratorTester.)
Bring over some API documentation from []

As currently defined, the hashcode of every unordered EndpointPair which is a self-loop is zero! This is particularly not good for graphs with many self-loops, such as the transitive closure graph, where every node has an incident self-loop. Change hash to use + instead of ^ (this still preserves the property of symmetry, even with overflow).
Suppress an intentional type mismatch.
Add new RangeSet methods accepting Iterable<Range<C>>.
Allow MemoizingSupplier to release its delegate to the GC where possible.
Update the Guava tagline on github.
Add @SafeVarargs to some methods Lists.
Optimize allocation in nonCancellationPropagating
Shuffling from internal-only change.
Fixes a documentation error regarding the return type/value
Prepare for Public Suffic List update, which removes the '!' rule that this file was using.
Update Public Suffix List.
Stop stripping @LazyInit annotations. The annotation has been released in public Error Prone.
Add JDK Deque implementations to Queue tests.
Make Charsets.ISO_8859_1 GwtCompatible. Also run google-java-format over the files.
graphs_explained.md: file being added to facilitate reviewed changes to https://github.com/google/guava/wiki/GraphsExplained.
Update to GWT 2.8.0-rc3.
Move ForwardingBlockingDeque into c.g.c.u.c.
Graph[Builder].java et al.: fix representation of angle brackets in Javadoc.  *sigh*
Shuffling from internal-only change.
Update to GWT 2.8.0
Fix bad Javadoc tags.
Lint Javadoc for HTML and syntax, and fix errors. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=137191293
Shuffling from internal-only change.
Start on documenting Iterables to explain the connection to Streams.
Fix links to murmurhash3.cpp
Make AtomicLongMap serializable. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=137404691
Make Forwarding[Listenable]Future GwtCompatible.
Mark Utf8 as emulated, since it has @GwtIncompatible methods.
Migrate from deprecated Guava APIs to replacements:  Objects.firstNonNull() -> MoreObjects.firstNonNull()  Objects.ToStringHelper -> MoreObjects.ToStringHelper
Update README to point to 20.0 as the latest release and update version numbers to 21.0-SNAPSHOT.
Fix link to Release 20
Fix a couple things in README.
Fix the extra space that shows up in ValueGraph's javadoc summary.
Add ImmutableList.sortedCopyOf.
fixes serialization errors when serializing a RegularImmutableAsList
Introduce InternerBuilder, which allows tweaking of the concurrency level of the to-be-built Interner. ------------- Created by MOE: https://github.com/google/moe MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=137825551
Fix some typos in guava/*
Make Ints.{to,from}ByteArray GWT compatible.
Add @since for Interners.Builder.
Remove emulated=true.  The class no longer needs to be emulated since there's nothing GwtIncompatible in it.
Fix typo in comments
fix warning on eclipse
Fixes a reference cycle between WeakValueEntry instances and their WeakValueReference.
Removes unnecessary (and unsafe) @Weak annotation that is causing crashes on iOS.
Release Java 8 changes to Guava.

message: Change travis config to not try to build on JDK7.
Fix JDK8 compilation errors in non-test code.
Add Multimaps.toMultimap(keyFunction, valueFunction, multimapSupplier) collector.
Simplify some Table implementation details.
Fix links to javadoc.io for Maven Javadoc Plugin
Fix ForwardingMultimapTest
Use a newer JDK 8 for travis build
Remove a redundant statement in TreeRangeMap.remove().
Continue uploading snapshots now that we're building only with JDK 8.
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 138114495.
Make SloppyTearDown.logger private.
Open source Comparators.
Note that Guava for Java 8 is coming.
Go back to Collections.sort() instead of List.sort() to eliminate difference between forks, since the former just delegates to the latter anyway.

Defer overlap checking in ImmutableRange{Set,Map}.Builder to the build() call, which matches the behavior in ImmutableMap.Builder and allows significantly faster handling of the case where ranges are inserted in predictable order.
Update link to GWT docs that died with Google Code.
Warn about overriding Converter.reverse().
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 56995761.
Fix some typos in guava-[gwt,testlib,tests]/*
Make some AbstractMapBasedMultimap helper methods static.  (As part of the process, make Sets.unmodifiableNavigableSet GWT-compatible, as NavigableSet is no longer an issue.)
Improve the Spliterator of Multimap values-for-key collections.
Add mapWithIndex overloads mapping IntStream -> Stream, etc.
Add a value-merging collector for ImmutableTable.
Add mutable Table collector to Tables, including a version with a merge function to match Collectors.toMap and ImmutableMap.toImmutableMap.
Add @Beta to the ImmutableTable collectors.
Include java.lang.Lang from java.util.Util. This is necessary now that our java.util contains classes that use java.lang.InterruptedException.
Use ForwardingWrapperTester in Forwarding*MultimapTest.
Reflect Navigable* support in GWT in TreeMultimap.
Document and deprecate mutations on SetView, which already documents its unmodifiability, as suggested by cushon@.

Fix two bugs in MinMaxPriorityQueue (introduced in [] First is a bug in removeAt(int) that sometimes causes the wrong element to be removed. Second is a bug that sometimes causes certain elements to be iterated over more than once if elements were removed during iteration.

Remove some misleading interruption docs: - Our interruption behavior doesn't fully match the JDK. My point in CL 23833126 was that both AbstractFuture and the JDK implementations throw if the thread was interrupted *before* the get() call as well as during. But:   - We differ from the JDK in a different area: We throw InterruptedException even if the get() call wouldn't have had to wait. (We see this as a feature: Since the task is apparently cancelled anyway, we might as well take this opportunity to abort.)   - My phrasing may be equally misleading in the other direction: It may suggest that get() throws if the thread was *ever* interrupted in the past. More generally, by changing the phrasing at all, I may be suggesting a change in behavior where none exists. - InterruptedException support is probably in some sense "optional," but there's no reason to call it out as specifically optional for AbstractFuture.

Avoid garbage allocation in simple hashBytes calls with Murmur3.
Delete com.google.math.Sample.
FluentFuture.
Fixes incorrectly-ordered arguments to method calls ([]
Fix @since tag.
Reorganize abstract HashFunction and Hasher implementations to simplify common.hash and potentially prepare for exposing these skeletal implementations.
PredecessorsFunction, SuccessorsFunction: remove @GoogleInternal annotation, now that we've resolved the "what type should the method return?" question.
Update Public Suffix List.
Increase timeout.
Upgrade Truth to 0.33.
In 4 files, manually include a TestCase in its own suite(). This lets the open-source build run those tests.
Run nested classes in the open-source build.

Fixes incorrectly-ordered arguments to calls to assertEquals ([] This change has been automatically generated by an Error Prone check that detects incorrect argument ordering on calls to assertEquals-style methods. See []
Reduce sizes of exhaustive/random MinMaxPriorityQueue tests; they're taking way too long.
Disable some tests externally until GWT releases a version with the problematic bug fixed.
Propagate cancellation for Futures.inCompletionOrder
Resurrect SingletonImmutableList on server side only.
Adding ByteBuffer support to Hashing APIs.
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 158168944.
Add @ReflectionSupport to AggregateFutureState, AtomicDouble and InterruptibleTask.
Update Javadoc plugin to a version that understands the Java 9 version scheme: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-442
Under Java 8, use Math.nextDown instead of FpUtils.nextDown.
Adding ByteBuffer support to Hashing APIs. Rollforward now that broken user is fixed.
Skip static methods, like the forthcoming Set.of.
Don't expect java.ext.dirs under Java 9.
Mark Immutable(IntLongDouble)Array with the errorprone @Immutable annotation
Move all surefire configuration to the parent pom.
Use a newer version of Mockito, as necessary for Java 9.
Recognize Java-9-style version strings.
Abstract common.graph classes: add Javadoc warnings that methods implemented in these classes should not be overridden without cause.
Add toString() to some Future subclasses.
Have ImmutableMap go back to using a specialized singleton implementation for size = 1 maps.
Test Android code on Travis with two different environments to hopefully avoid timeouts
Change implementation of Byte/CharSource.isEmpty to avoid opening a stream when the size of the source is known to be >0.
Expand common.hash ByteBuffer support, adding a default AbstractHasher hashBytes implementation and expanding HashTestUtils to test more about the hashing of ByteBuffers.
MutableGraph.java: fix Javadoc link.
Optimize murmur3_32 hashString(CharSequence, UTF_8) to unroll the Utf8 directly into the hasher rather than converting it to a byte array.
Don't fail tests just because we can't securely delete recursively.
Output "java.util.Map.Entry" under Java 9, as the JDK does. Under previous JDKs, we continue to output "java.util.Map.java.util.Map.Entry," just as those JDKs do.
Marginally improve what Maven prints for javac errors (by upgrading maven-compiler-plugin).
Prepare common.graph for Java-8-specific changes.
Stop claiming that Guava has only one dependency.
Fix typo in FluentIterable#stream javadoc

Network.java: fork edgeConnecting() for java7/Android: * current/.../Network.java now provides   java.util.Optional<E> edgeConnecting(N, N)   E edgeConnectingOrNull(N, N) * java7/.../Network.java now provides   E edgeConnectingOrNull(N, N)
common.graph tests: unify some duplicate constructs (enums, methods, constants) and put them in TestUtil.java.
Fix doc which was incorrect in the null case, and add a few words about a behavior some users have been depending on (that it intercepts NPE and CCE).
Update Guava to depend on Truth 0.34.
Only get values from Map in Maps.immutableEnumMap once.  Fixes https://github.com/google/guava/issues/2854 .
Prepare for Java-8-specific changes to common.hash.
AbstractNetwork: add a functionally correct (if not super-efficient) implementation of edgesConnecting(), because it's easy to do wrong.
Fix Javadoc missing "code" typos.
Add BloomFilter collector, now that common.hash is forked.  Finishes off https://github.com/google/guava/issues/2810.
Propagate CL 160170507's doc changes to the java7 branch.
Remove extra punctuation in single-sentence @return
hasEdge(): rename to hasEdgeConnecting(), remove @GoogleInternal annotation, and add to Network as well.
Fix AbstractFuture.toString()'s message on futures that failed. Expanded unit tests to match the expected strings more completely.
Remove unnecessary from() calls for things that are already FluentIterables
Add simple `closed` and `closedOpen` ContiguousSet factories for int and long.
Open up pendingToString()
Add cross-references to sibling Preconditions and Verify methods, to aid discoverability.
Add @since for pendingToString().
Add an Automatic-Module-Name manifest entry.
Update code.google.com link to github in Murmur3Hash32Test
Remove static map allocation and map lookup in base.Defaults.
Fix broken {@link} comment in AbstractFuture.
Fix some more broken {@link} comments.
Prepare common.graph for GWT/j2cl usage.
Throw IllegalArgumentException if a loop in the causal chain is detected in Throwables.getCausalChain() and Throwables.getRootCause().
ValueGraph.edgeValue*: change from * V edgeValue(), V edgeValueOrDefault() to * Optional<V> edgeValue(), V edgeValueOrNull()

message: Make documentation on iteration order more explicit.
Add @SafeVarargs to Predicates.or(Predicate<? super T>...).
Don't include the toString() of the future if it completes while the timeout expires.
Add @since 23.0 to new (or with new return type) edgeValue methods in ValueGraph.
Fix >100 violation in ImmutableMap doc update.
Make RateLimiter.create parameter order consistent.
Switch to using AtomicReference, since only one field needs CAS.
ValueGraph.java: restore edgeValueOrNull() to edgeValueOrDefault().
ValueGraph.java: remove bogus @since 23.0 on edgeValueOrDefault.
Optimize CharSource.wrap(CharSequence) for when the CharSequence is a String

common.graph: create (package-protected) ForwardingValueGraph and ForwardingNetwork classes, and use those (and ForwardingGraph) to simplify the implementation of the Transposed* inner classes in Graphs.
Optimize CharStreams.copy to take advantage of known Readable/Appendable types.
Shutdown the original executor in getExitingScheduledExecutorService.
Add @SafeVarargs to Predicates.and(Predicate<? super T>...).
Update Public Suffix List.
Short-circuit null check in Throwables#lazyStackTraceIsLazy
Add submitAsync and scheduleAsync methods, to ease the deprecation of Futures.dereference
Implement ByteSource.asCharSource(charset).read() using the decoding string constructor instead of streaming the contents into a StringBuilder.
Add deprecation notice to Futures.dereference
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 162220754.

Rollforward [] which was rolled back in [] because it caused some tests using appengine to fail with IOExceptions when calling FileInputStream.available().  The workaround in the rollforward is to not call the method.  The one case where we were calling it we had actually already called a similar method, so trying again doesn't seem valuable anyway.
Use specialized spliterators for Primitives.asList utilities.  Addresses https://github.com/google/guava/issues/2874 .
Fix interruption leak in submitAsync and whenAllComplete().callAsync().
Add @ForOverride to AbstractFuture.afterDone now that https://github.com/google/error-prone/issues/342 is fixed.
Forgot to specify equals().
Plug ImmutableIntArray in Ints, etc.
Super-minor cleanup to AggregateFuture
Fix a bug in AbstractFuture.setFuture
Warn a little more about weakKeys resulting in == key comparisons, even in the asMap view.
Fix an interruption bug from CL 162649353, but do so in a way that doesn't reintroduce yet another bug that that CL fixed.
Remove some methods that are scheduled for removal in 23.0, along with one that was apparently scheduled for removal in 21.0.

message: Take advantage of suppressed exceptions in ServiceManager now that Guava is on Java 8.
Use diamond operator.
Mention 23.0-rc1 in Guava README.
Remove Maven version badge from README.
Add notes about Java8 to UnsignedBytes, UnsignedInts, and UnsignedLongs.
Add collectors for ImmutableRangeSet and ImmutableRangeMap.
Avoid importing ImmutableList from Ordering.
Make ListenableScheduledFuture GwtCompatible.
Shuffling from internal-only change.
Change CacheBuilder constructor modifier to private, and rewrite corresponding tests
Minor fix in comment.
Update removal data for dereference().
Avoid dependency on CharMatcher in BaseEncoding.
Catch NoClassDefFoundError and generic Error, the types thrown by JVM8 and by modern versions of Android.
Update Guava README for 23.0 and update snapshot versions.
Suppress tests broken by CL 164180554's emulator upgrade to API level 15.
Fix broken Javadoc link in UnsignedLongs.toString(long)
Ignore the lazyStackTraceIsLazy test on Java 9, for now.
Fix typo in AbstractService log message.
In ImmutableCollection.ArrayBasedBuilder, keep a forceCopy flag to allow builder types to force a copy even if the entire array has not been used.
common.graph: remove j2cl annotations, as no one's using it from j2cl, it has no immediate prospective users, and it doesn't support Network-related capabilities anyway.
Add ImmutableList.builderWithExpectedSize API.

Test that a failed/cancelled input doesn't cause us to cancel other inputs. (It's debatable whether that's the long-term behavior we want, but we should at least document that current behavior properly.)
Add Immutable{Map,BiMap}.builderWithExpectedSize API.
Fix javadoc link by including package name.
Polishing
Fixes #2905
Add ImmutableSet.builderForExpectedSize.  Currently, the implementation is that if and only if a size is specified up front, the builder starts generating the hash table online and deduping elements.
Fix @since tags for collectors that didn't make 23.0.
Update Guava's JUnit dependencies to 4.11 (the version in [])

message: Store the CancellationException.class (as we do in other tests), not the cause of the CancellationException.
catch (SomeException e) {   // Expected }
Remove a dangling closing bracket from Javadoc
Use diamond operator for all test targets except 'collect'
Use diamond for collect tests.
[guava concurrent] Added MoreExecutors.sequentialExecutor(), and its documentation.
Specifically instruct people who are calling dereference(transform(...)) to call transformAsync(...).
ImmediateFuture.toString() implementation to provide the returned value or exception. Provides for all ImmediateFutures implementation the same syntax that AbstractFuture uses.
Update Public Suffix list.
Javadoc update when delegate throws exception.
Update Guava's dependency on Truth to 0.35.
Add java.util.Optional and its derivatives (OptionalInt, OptionalLong, OptionalDouble) to ArbitraryInstances and FreshValueGenerator.
fix typo
Streams.concat: Propagate close to sources streams

[guava concurrent] Renamed SerializingExecutor to SequentialExecutor. Turned SerializingExecutor into a proxy to SequentialExecutor so two Components classes that directly use it have a chance to catch up.
Remove redundant calls to NullPointerTester#setDefault
Set version numbers to 24.0-jre-SNAPSHOT.
Remove @CanIgnoreReturnValue from Listening*ExecutorService. Users should do something with the returned Futures, if only log failures.
MOE strip the "public" from SortedLists' member enums.
Migrate Executor-less Futures callback methods to the ones with an Executor, while applying MoreExecutors.directExecutor() for identical behavior.
Fix parameter comments that don't match the formal parameter name
Rewrite EnumMultiset to be directly backed by an E[] and an int[], avoiding allocation of boxing objects.
Add @CanIgnoreReturnValue to EnumMultiset#add
Fix edge case in EnumMultiset.remove
The documentation of PredecessorsFunction and SuccessorsFunction now makes it clear that null nodes are forbidden.
Add note about nodes being valid Map keys to PredecessorsFunction and SuccessorsFunction.
Make ClassPath search the contents of the "java.class.path" system property for the system class loader in Java 9.
Fix tests that assume Class.getClassLoader() returns a URLClassLoader so that they can call getURLs() to instead parse the "java.class.path" system property.
Add Traverser API without implementation.
Clarify some docs on Ordering+Comparators
Add reverse methods to all primitive arrays in common.primitives.
Add sorting methods for the unsigned primitives in common.primitives.
Propagate close for to the inputs of Streams.zip and Streams.mapWithIndex
Merge pull request #2942 from google/sync-master-2017/09/18
Fix documentation for checkArgument and checkState
Add @GoogleInternal propagateCancellation to Futures.
Add sortDescending methods in common.primitives.
Make propagateCancellation helpers @GoogleInternal.
Add the same overloads that Preconditions has in Verify.
Fix space complexity in forTree() documentation.
Revert parts of CL 33393713 that changed Splitter.on(",") tests to redundant Splitter.on(',') tests. Use COMMA_SPLITTER in more remaining Splitter.on(',') tests.
Traverser.java: tweak the forGraph() and forTree() documentation to make memory use a bit more clear.
Implement Traverser.forGraph().breadhFirst().
common.graph: fix formatting error in Graph/ValueGraph/Network Javadoc.
Throwables#lazyStackTrace unsupported on IBM JDK 6
Make common.collect spliterators backed by an int-indexed function correctly splittable.
Fix Guava version number re. BloomFilter thread safety.
Slightly bump the fpp to prevent OOM under JDK9.
Fixed a typo in the Predicates class documentation.
Change version number in pom files from 24.0 to HEAD(-jre/android-SNAPSHOT).
Change "@since 24.0" to "@since NEXT".
Change Futures.dereference removal from Guava 25.0 to January 2018.
Update Preconditions overloads that were added in 20.0 to have @since 20.0 and new Verify overloads to have @since NEXT.
Update @since tags to @since 23.1.
Fix some random Error Prone warnings.
Update set_version.sh to handle new versioning scheme and ignore snapshot versions since those are no longer chaning.
[guava concurrent] Removed the executeFirst() method from SequentialExecutor, and its test case. Switched the internal representation of the task queue back to Queue from Deque.
[guava concurrent] Updated a comment in ListenerCallQueue to point at SequentialExecutor instead of the deprecated SerializingExecutor wrapper interface.
Update Verify.java @since NEXT tags to 23.1.
We test on Ice Cream Sandwich now, not Gingerbread.
Minor noop updates to Future and TimeUnit in preparation of moving.

[guava concurrent] Removed the now-unused suspend() and resume() methods from SequentialExecutor. Removed the special-case visibility. Marked SequentialExecutor final. Removed the now-unused SerializingExecutor migration interface. Updated Javadoc to remove references to the now-gone methods.
Fix Escaper.java comment typo.
Remove CountDownLatch emulation
For clarity, re-apply @Beta to the CharMatcher constants.
Document that we're no longer removing stable APIs.
Remove removal dates for non-@Beta deprecations.
Update "current release" to 23.1. Remove API diffs that are available from the release page.
Implement Traverser.forGraph().depthFirst*().
Update the farmHashFingerprint64() javadoc to specify how FarmHash's numeric fingerprint is encoded by HashCode#asBytes().
Update README to refer to HEAD-jre/android-SNAPSHOT for the snapshot versions.
ValueGraph: fix implementation of edgeValueOrDefault(). Also fixed tests to guard against similar future regressions.
Documentation improvement: Clarify disambiguities around post-order/pre-order.
All javadoc examples now use the same example graph (also matches the one in the unit test).
Handle InheritableThreadLocals correctly on Java 9.
Make sure that local task reference is retained in objc
Add JPMS module name
Rollback [] for AtomicDouble(Array) that added jdk5 support.
Implement Traverser.forTree().breadthFirst().
Implement Traverser.forTree().depthFirst*().
Update Public Suffix data.
Fix bug where ImmutableSortedMap could accept a null key/value pair.
Expand BiMap test suite for forcePut operation, and fix a newly revealed bug in the HashBiMap status quo.
Expand BiMapTestSuiteBuilder's tests for setValue calls on entries (which get run on both forward and backward BiMaps).
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 163355688.
ValueGraphTest.java: add a few checks to make sure that we're properly exercising both null and non-null default values.
Fix links.
Deprecate matchers which cannot work as expected because the API does not support supplementary code points. Clarify some API docs. Point to ICU4J for an actual Unicode library.
Document that negate() @Overrides under Java 8 but not under Java 7.

Don't log until static state is fully set up. This prevents a (hypothetical, to my knowledge) bug where a device exhibiting the samsung reflection bug would fail to fall back if an installed logger called a Futures method inline.

Update deprecation messages for the CharMatcher constants to match the new deprecation messages on the factory methods while still suggesting that the factory methods be used rather than the constants if needed.
Make the copying done for guava-gwt not verbose.

Remove unnecessary volatile; this boolean value is only relevant if the executor runs the provided runnable inline, which means that the write will always be visible to the read in the catch() statement.
Update hardcoded digit() and invisible() from Unicode 6.3 to Unicode 9.
Update latest release to 23.2.

Update AtomicDouble in Java 7 to use AtomicLong directly instead of AtomicLongFieldUpdater.  This is a relatively simple way of protecting against bugs like the Samsung bug, and clm@ and I agreed that the simplification over what e.g. AbstractFuture has had to do was worth the extra allocation.
Update hasPublicSuffix javadoc
Fix Striped.lazyWeakReadWriteLock so that holding on to just the read or just the write lock will not allow the ReadWriteLock to be garbage collected, which many users find surprising.
Strip the public from ListenerCallQueue.Event in open source.  It's not actually visible, anyway.
Traverser: Throw IAE if startNode is not part of the graph and add tests for empty graph case and disjoint trees (forest) case.
Add test for a graph with a single root.
Using Object instead of a specific type irritates some thread safety tests.  Fix that.
Add the notion of RegistrySuffix to InternetDomainName.
RELNOTES=Introduce MoreExecutors.newSequentialExecutor, the new name of sequentialExecutor.
Fix minor spelling errors in tests.
Use whichever version of nextDown is available.
Deprecate [Binary]TreeTraverser.
Avoid using WeakSafeReadWriteLock when not using weak references
Detect HtmlUnit's broken sorting, and skip our tests that depend on proper sorting, at least when running our GWT tests in the open-source build.
Set all @since NEXT to @since 23.3.
Add Referrer-Policy to HTTP Headers.
Upgrade GWT version to 2.8.2, plus:
Update readme to show new current version 23.3.
Add @since tags to some nested types.
Fix links to JSR305, and start linking to JDK 9.

In Java 7 branch, don't bother using Iterators.forArray in RegularImmutable{List,Set}.  The default ImmutableList.listIterator implementation amounts to the same thing, an AbstractIndexedListIterator delegating to the array.
Add private constructor to Traverser.
Remove @GwtCompatible annotations from classes in the hash package, which have no corresponding .gwt.xml file.
[guava concurrent] Upstreamed a modified form of the modified interruption behaviour from a fork of SerializingExecutor. Documented and tested the behaviour thoroughly.
Make a small change to README.md to make it simpler to auto-update.
Clear the interrupt bit at the end of the test.
Print the actual output of failed tests.
Run tests in a deterministic order.
Actually export print_surefire_reports.sh.
Optimize ImmutableCollection.Builder.addAll(ImmutableCollection) to use System.arraycopy when possible.
Wait longer for the interrupt to happen.
Don't issue a warning for the lack of srcs in the "main" guava-tests jar.
Remove redirectTestOutputToFile from guava-testlib configuration.
Run nested classes for real this time.
Make all "Tester" classes *end* with "Tester," and simplify our exclusions accordingly.
Fix range typo in comments of subRangeMap.
Support for empty ArrayTable.
Remove no-op check.
Add Files.fileTraverser().
Add MoreFiles.fileTraverser().
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 174865821.
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 174856751.
Prepare for release 23.4.
Reduce iterations for MinMaxPriorityQueueTest under GWT.
Don't construct thousands of strings.
Don't release guava-tests to Maven Central
Correct gender off-by-one error. :)
Make package-list files available to the android backport, too.
Roll forward.
Roll forward.
Claim that ImmutableCollection classes should still be preferred over Java 9 factories like `Set.of`. https://github.com/google/guava/issues/2969
Update docs that refer to the removed `suspensions` field.
Refactor file tree children logic to separate method just like in MoreFiles.
Graduate Verify and VerifyException from Beta as requested here: https://github.com/google/guava/issues/2409
Annotate Cache with @CompatibleWith
Try out @OverridingMethodsMustInvokeSuper, and remove some unnecessary work in AbstractMapTester.
Import Map.Entry almost everywhere.
Migrate from jsr305's @Immutable to Error Prone's.
Remove @ThreadSafe and @NotThreadSafe annotations.
Fully qualify some references to javax.annotation.Nullable in files that will likely soon refer to both that Nullable and the Checker Framework's.
Carry @CanIgnoreReturnValue over to new methods.

Mutable{Graph, Network, ValueGraph}.java: tighten the contract for the edge-adding methods.  The contract now states that if the specified nodes are not already present in the graph, they are silently added.  (Removes the option of throwing in this case.)
Fix inheriting docs from the JDK.
Migrate usage of Files.fileTreeTraverser() to Files.fileTraverser().
Carry @CanIgnoreReturnValue over to new methods.
Update Public Suffix data.
Deprecate Files.fileTreeTraverser() and MoreFiles.directoryTreeTraverser().
Add Checker Framework to dependencies.
Add ImmutableMap.getOrDefault() in the Android branch.
Prepare for release 23.5.
Don't use recursion in MultiInputStream.read().
Adding [Server-Timing] HTTP header.
Add missing @Nullable annotation to ForwardingSortedSet.unsafeCompare(Object, Object).
Add missing @Nullable to Preconditions.
Add missing @Nullable to Finalizer.
Promote ReferenceEntry to a top-level class for weird reasons.
Depend on error_prone_annotations 2.1.3.
Migrate from jsr305's @CheckReturnValue to Error Prone's.
Migrate from jsr305's @GuardedBy and @OverridingMethodsMustInvokeSuper to Error Prone's.
Add missing @Nullable to the fields in ImmutableSet.java
Remove public constructors from SimpleTimeLimiter.
Schedule assignableFrom for deletion.
Change "late 2017" removal date to January 2018.
Add @Nullable to MoreObjects.
Update oss-parent to version 9.
Automated g4 rollback of changelist 177586281.
Make getUnchecked available under GWT.
Remove maven-gpg-plugin configuration from Guava's pom.

Remove public constructors from SimpleTimeLimiter.

message: Miscellanous followup to CL 177814345:
Depend on checker-compat-qual instead of checker-qual.
Recognize @NullableDecl in NullPointerTester and friends.
